article.description: Cierra Bravard had 21 points and 15 rebounds and Florida State held on to beat Wake Forest 82-79.
article.headline: Seminoles blow lead but win third straight
article.linkText: Streaking Florida State holds off Wake Forest
article.story:
WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. --  Cierra Bravard had 21 points and 15 rebounds and Florida State (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) held on to beat Wake Forest 82-79 on Thursday night.

Alexa Deluzio added 18 points for the Seminoles (21-5, 9-2 Atlantic Coast Conference), who allowed most of a 15-point lead to slip away before winning their third straight.

The victory, coupled with No. 7 Duke's loss to Maryland (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP), moves the Seminoles into a tie for first place in the ACC with the Blue Devils and Miami (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 13 AP).

Sandra Garcia scored 17 points for Wake Forest (12-15, 3-8). Chelsea Douglas added 13 and her layup with two seconds left pulled the Demon Deacons within three.

Lakevia Boykin had 12 points and Brittany Waters added 11 for Wake Forest, which has lost two straight and eight of 11.

Courtney Ward added 13 points for Florida State, which went up 46-31 on Bravard's free throw with 18:17 left. Brooke Thomas' 3-pointer roughly a minute later started Wake Forest's comeback.
